'''Bassem Sabry''' ({{lang-ar|باسم صبري}}) 
(25 October 1982 – 29 April 2014)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/30/bassem-sabry-egypt-revolution-dies|title=Bassem Sabry, a voice of Egypt's 2011 revolution, dies in accident|date=30 April 2014|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> was an Egyptian journalist, [[blog]]ger, and [[civil rights]] campaigner who had reported extensively on the [[Egyptian Crisis (2011–present)|Egyptian Revolution]].
<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":0">[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/04/egyptian-blogger-bassem-sabry-dies-2014430122918774191.html Egyptian blogger Bassem Sabry dies – Middle East]. Al Jazeera English. Retrieved on 10 June 2014.</ref><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/04/30/bassem-sabry-dead_n_5238521.html Bassem Sabry Dead: Egyptian Blogger And Civil Rights Activist Dies After Fall From Balcony]. Huffingtonpost.com (30 April 2014). Retrieved on 10 June 2014.</ref>
<ref>[https://www.vox.com/2014/4/29/5666200/on-bassem-sabry On Bassem Sabry]. Vox (29 April 2014). Retrieved on 10 June 2014.</ref> [[Al-Monitor]] eulogized him as being "widely considered to be among the most incisive and respected analysts of the country’s politics."<ref name=r1>{{cite web|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2014/04/bassem-sabry-death-mourned.html|title=Al Monitor mourns Bassem Sabry|date=29 April 2014|accessdate=30 April 2014}}
</ref> 

